		"description": {
			"value": "<p><em>Wondrous Item - Legendary</em></p><p><em>A magic item like this counts as magical for overcoming effects.</em></p><p><strong>Trap Creature</strong></p><p><strong>Action</strong> - 1 Creature (60 ft.)</p><p><em>Trigger: </em>The flask is empty, target a creature you can see within 60 feet that is native to another plane. </p><p> <strong>[[/save WIS 17]]{Wisdom Save (DC 17)}</strong></p><ul><li><p><strong>Failure:</strong> Target is trapped in the flask (&amp;reference[Advantage] if it has been trapped by this flask before). The flask holds only one creature; a trapped creature doesn’t age or need to breathe, eat, or drink.</p></li><li><p><strong>Success: </strong>No effect.</p></li></ul><p><strong>Release Creature</strong></p><p><strong>Action</strong> - 1 Hour</p><p><strong>Summoning</strong></p><ul><li><p>Removing the stopper releases the trapped creature. It obeys your commands for 1 hour, understanding you even if it doesn’t share a language; if given no commands or only self-harmful ones, it defends itself but takes no other actions. After 1 hour it acts according to its nature.</p></li><li><p>An <em>@UUID[Compendium.elkan5e.elkan5e-spells.Item.DtqyQCHrAX96VclO]{Identify}</em> spell reveals if the flask contains a creature; the only way to know which creature is to open it. A newly found flask may already contain a GM-chosen creature.</p></li></ul><section class=\"secret\" id=\"foundry-secret-1\"><p><strong>Foundry Note</strong></p><p>This item has one limited use for tracking whether or not a creature has been trapped in the flask.</p><p>The <strong>Add Trapped Creature</strong> activity expends a usage to indicate it is currently full.</p><p>The <strong>Release Trapped Creature</strong> activity is a summon activity which restores a usage to indicate it can now contain another creature. You can edit the activity, change to the \"Summon\" tab and drag the captured creature's Actor onto the tab so it can be summoned later.</p></section>",
